The paper discusses training machine-learning models at low precision, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on developing a framework for training models with end-to-end low precision, which is a topic that is likely to be classified under these sub-categories.
